title: NOT
description: Returns TRUE if the provided logical value evaluates to FALSE; otherwise, returns FALSE.

parameters.name: logical
parameters.description: The logical value or expression to evaluate.

examples:
NOT(Priority == "High")
-- Returns TRUE if Priority is not equal to "High".
-- For example, if Priority is "Medium" or "Low", the result is TRUE.
-- If Priority is "High", the result is FALSE.

tips.text: It functions the same as the ! operator.
